# Date display format

Every **user-facing** date in the UI must be shown as `dd/MM/yyyy` (zero-padded day and month).

## Do

- Format display values with `formatDateShort` from `frontend/src/lib/transform.js` (already outputs `dd/MM/yyyy`).
- Pass ISO strings, sheet dates, or `Date` objects through `formatDateShort` / `parseDate` — never render raw API/ISO dates.

```jsx
// ❌ BAD — raw ISO or sheet value
<td>{g.date}</td>

// ✅ GOOD
<td>{formatDateShort(g.date)}</td>
```

## Do not

- Do not invent a second formatter; extend `formatDateShort` if the shared helper needs a change.
- Do not use `toLocaleDateString`, `toISOString().slice(0, 10)`, or locale defaults for **display**.
- HTML `<input type="date">` values stay ISO (`yyyy-MM-dd`) for the control; only the **shown** text must be `dd/MM/yyyy`.
